    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "everything is just so quiet now. i walk into the kitchen and i still expect to hear him making coffee or the sound of his keys on the counter. it’s like I’m living in a museum of a life that died. there’s no point to any of this. i'm just going through the motions in a house that feels like a tomb.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
